-- MGIC posts smaller loss as fewer homeowners default
-- By Tanya Agrawal in Bangalore
-- Thu Jan 23, 2014 07:18AM EST
-- None



Jan 23 (Reuters) - Mortgage insurer MGIC Investment Corp <MTG.N> posted a smaller quarterly loss as fewer U.S. homeowners defaulted in a recovering housing market.

MGIC reported a fourth-quarter loss of $1.4 million, and broke even on a per share basis, compared with a loss of $386.7 million, or $1.91 per share, a year earlier. [ID:nPnbSVR0r]